<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-685313" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/YSFON.png?resize=412%2C552&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="412" height="552" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/YSFON.png?w=412&amp;ssl=1 412w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/YSFON.png?resize=224%2C300&amp;ssl=1 224w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/YSFON.png?resize=43%2C58&amp;ssl=1 43w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/YSFON.png?resize=145%2C194&amp;ssl=1 145w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/YSFON.png?resize=97%2C130&amp;ssl=1 97w" sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Youth Sports Federation of Nigeria (YSFON) has announced the postponement of this year’s Ramat Cup. The tournament which is the oldest grassroots football competition in the country was earlier scheduled to hold at the Kano Pillars Stadium from February 5~13, 2021. Announcing the postponement, National Secretary of the Federation, Patrick Okpavuerhe, said the decision was taken because of the COVID~19 pandemic which is still witnessing a spike in many states of the Federation. While expressing regrets and the inconveniences the postponement might cause participants, he explained that once a new date is agreed on with the host state, Kano, it will be communicated to all states. Meanwhile, YSFON National President Dr Yusuf Gawuna who also doubles as the Deputy Governor of Kano State said that all logistics for a successful tournament had been put in place before the postponement. Vanguard News Nigeria The Youth Sports Federation of Nigeria, YSFON has concluded plans to stage this year’s edition of the annual Late General Murtala Ramat Mohammed Football Competition tagged Ramat Cup for U-16 boys and U-18 girls in Kano, the Kano State capital between from February 12 to 16, 2017. February 12, 2017 In "Sports" The Youth Sports Federation Of Nigeria YSFON has concluded preparations to resurrect and launch new tournaments that would avail youths in the nation opportunities to develop their talents and contribute their quota to the development of the society. February 24, 2016 In "Sports" Youth Sports Federation of Nigeria( YSFON) has commended the Kano State Government for it’s grassroots sports development programme; saying it’s happy with the efforts the state government is making towards having a successful 37th edition of the annual Ramat Cup for U-16 boys slated for February 13-21 in Kano State.… February 8, 2020 In "Sports"